    "client_msg_id": "873a4812-5ae1-4ef4-b831-d52ae60f3761",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I've been meaning to write it up -- but basically, I worked on a fork of the Xanadu project (XanaDesk) for a summer and created a version of it in Flash while pursuing my PhD. I succeeded in visualizing transclusions, implementing his permascroll concept and various link types, including visualizing documents as \"wands.\" I did recommend using HTML and web standards, and with the death of Flash, it'll be difficult to show off the project, but I've been meaning to make a video of it.",
    "user": "U022U66AKMW",
    "ts": "1621272508.179300",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
